values: <font color="blue">I bought some chips and salsa.. someone ate my freakin chips!  I don't really like to drink salsa.

I was driving to WAL*MART today, and listening to public radio.. they said power was out and affecting businesses on the east side of town. So I assumed WAL*MART was one of them. Sure enough the parking lot was nearly empty but I had gone all that way, so I wanted to make something out of it. So I sat in the parking lot and just watched how many people would get out of their car, help their kids out of the car, put them in shopping carts and walk all the way to the door and be told that the store was closed until the power came back on. That parking lot is usually full and you have to park far away. Wouldn't you realize that when you see all the WAL*MART employees standing outside, people walking back to their cars empty handed and the empty parking lot? I heard one lady from outside my car, ask a associate how long the power would be out.. because they would know.. I don't know, it was sorta amusing for a half hour. FOUR MORE DAYS! .. but who's counting?.. ME!!! I am going to watch the shit out of that DVD. Hope everyone is having a great week.. guess what!! tomorrow is friday! yay! Nooch! Jimmy

What can I say.. I'm broke. This weekend was pretty fun, for not having any money. Friday night, I went to Mel and Bob's and hung out with them and Josh and J.J. Jill went over there after work. Saturday night, I met up with Rick and Mindy at Rick's house.. Mel and Bob went there after they had some Khan's. We played a word game on the computer.. and watched the Family Guy Movie and hung out. Nice relaxing time. Thank you guys for the presents, They are all awesome! But you got way too much. Thank you though! I hope yall want to go out next weekend and do something.. Tonight I went over to my grandparents and had some cake. It was good! Chocolate cake with caramel filling and Cool Whip frosting. Mmm.. I'm bringing some of that for lunch tomorrow... hells yeah! Tomorrow I get to call up my car insurance company and have them change my policy. I'm gonna get a huge discount, reduction on my insurance policy. I can't wait. But just wanted to say thanks to them guys and such. It's been a good b-day so far, and it's not even here yet. naga nooch! Jimmy time for bed...

Back to the Future II So... If things in the future instantaniously changed around Jennifer and Einstein, when The Almanac was burned.. why didn't things in the future instantaniously change when old Biff gave himself the Almanac in the past? He was able to go back to the original future reality and bring back the DeLorean?

<font color="blue">Well, I've decided I am going back to the 1980's.  I am going to re-live the entire decade.  I remember not having to worry about things much.  Things seemed to be alot easier and slower paced.  The coolest toys existed, you got the whole summer off from school, and didn't have any obligations.  We were all so innocent and understanding then.  If you want to come with, I have room for 2 more.  I'm leaving tonight at midnight.  get ahold of me somehow.

So long,

J****1980*****\4/2\7/F\2/E\00/9\3/3\3/I\B/T\J/P\A/B\S/1992838490|.

I was really looking forward to hanging out with friends tonight. But I have gotten sick. I have a huge head cold. I woke up around noon today, but went right back to bed and got up around five o'clock. I have been completely worthless today, got nothing accomplished except for watching National Treasure tonight. Great movie. I love things about History. Last night I met Rick at Wendy's and we ate some dinner and looked around Best Buy for a while. I got a new cope of Fellowship of the Ring soundtrack. We went to his house and he let me use his wireless internet. Dang, things load and download fast! I got about 80 songs downloaded in no time. Thanks Rick. Bob and Mel came over after they were at TC's. I drove home around 1:30ish and nearly died about 10 times for falling asleep. I was almost home and the last time I nodded off, when I opened my eyes and almsost hit a skunk. So I swerved almost off the road and then I was totally awake for the last mile home. I don't want my car to smell like skunk. But now the interior smells like skunk.. great. Coach Jimmy's got money, but not much. I'm so poor right now. Shit. Oh well.. When in Rome. hope everyone is having a fantastic weekend. "The gray rain-curtain of this world rolls back, and all change to silver glass... And then you see it. White shores...and beyond. The far green country under a swift sunrise."

<font color="blue">sheesh...

ok, I layed down to take a short nap around 4 pm.. and it's now a little after midnight.. what the heck?!?  I wasn't tired.. or maybe i was.. I have found that having a fan on, while I am sleeping, puts me in a coma.  Don't know why that is.  oh well.

I am going to have to get a second job.  There's just something about staying busy during the fall/winter..  I want to get things paid off, and such.  Any ideas where I should apply?  I am just looking for a part time job, just to make a few hundred dollars more a week.  or as much as I can get :).

Dang.. I have been playing a lot of Xbox lately, mostly Battlefront.. That is the first Xbox game I ever bought, and it still isn't getting old.  Battlefront 2 is coming out November 1st, the same day as Revenge of the Sith's DVD.  That will be an expensive day.  

This weekend was fun!  Friday night, I met Mel and Bob at Sidelines and had some dinner.. then we went to Matt's party.  The band was ok, but they didn't know the words to "Sweet Home Alabama.."  who doesn't know the words to that?!?!?.. I didn't get home until 4am, which was 24 hours after I got up for work... so I was a little tired..  Saturday, I went over to Matty's Uncle's house, and watched him and his uncle play chess for about 3 hours..  that got kind of boring.. why invite me over watch that, and not include me..  I was a little pissed, but I guess I'm over it now.  After that I raced down to Mel and Bob's and we watched Viva La Bam.. and had some good chips.  good times.  Sunday, I went back over to Matt's and we watched some TV.. Family Guy was on.. that show is always funny!

I bought Sin City yesterday.  Damn! that movie was awesome.  I guess I'm mostly looking forward to owning Revenge of the Sith on DVD.  It could very well be, my most favorite movie of all time.

OH!.. The teen choice awards were on yesterday.  and Jon Heder (Napolean Dynamite) won for something, I can't remember.  But he said, in Napolean's voice. 'I wish you girls would cheer for me, like you cheered for Jesse McCartney.. more like Jesse McFartney.' he is so freakin funny!

Thursday tomorrow..

Bowling Friday.

I love weekends!

hope everyone is having a great week!


--Jimmy</font>

Directions: Type "(your name) is," with the quotes, into a Google search then pick out your favorite 10 responses. Copy, then repost your responses: "Jimmy" is a reference to James Maynard Keenan Jimmy is British slang for an injection of a narcotic drug, especially heroin Jimmy is also fast becoming a face on US TV. Jimmy is the shy Manchester teenager who is bullied by the bigger lads Jimmy is currently leading his own band, performing original and standard material. Jimmy is coming back to Canada after nine long years! Jimmy is forced to return to the trailer park where his mother (Kim Basinger) and little sister live. Jimmy is 8 years old and a third-generation heroin addict, a precocious little boy Jimmy is back at the Dragon Dojo using the jewel to try to find his father. Jimmy is forcing Superman to watch.

Today was a shitty day at work. I joke around with co-workers about quitting... well we all do... but today, I was 99.999999% on my way into the bosses office and telling him to "go fuck himself". But that's not me. I am not a person who would do that. I tend to keep things to myself, I know I probably shouldn't.. but I find it easier to fix problems on my own. I don't know if it's because nobody cares, or if I can fix it faster, because I know the source. I feel bad, because I was a real prick to a few people today. I am usually not a prick. I just hope tomorrow will be better and I can avoid my boss for most of the day. There are only a few people at work who can make my day better. I'm glad they are there, or I would probably be fired or I would be an asshole. When I got home today, I was bitching about work.. my mom said a few things.. and it made me realize, some things are not so bad, and could be worse. I love my mom. She's cool. hope everyone elses week is going great! "aisha yana" -jimmy

Well this was a fun weekend Friday night we had Mel and Bob's wedding rehersal. After that, the whole wedding party went to Buca. That place has some awesome food!!!... we sat around a huge table, in the Pope room. There was a bust of the Pope in the center of the table. He watched all of us eat. Saturday, was the wedding. FUN!. It was fun walking with Jill, I hope i didn't annoy her too much :) .. or anyone else for that matter. Good food at the reception! The cake was awesome!.. Reception dances are always great too! My legs and feet were so sore at midnight.. i stumbled out with Jill and Josh, *(thanks for bringing me back to my car)*... I was happy to be a part of their wedding. It was a very fun, and enlightening event. Today I got up early and brought my tux back to Men's Warehouse, my brother and I went to Best Buy for a while as well. got some stuff and came home. Later this afternoon, we went to see Charlie and the Chocolate Factory. It's hilarious and SO GOOD!... I can't wait to get that on DVD. and we also got to see the trailer for Corpse Bride.. another Tim Burton flick coming out.. looks like Nightmare Before Christmas.. yesss! I have tomorrow off, so I think I will be sitting around.. I'm actually gonna have a day off.. YESSS!!!.. I love days when I can just sleep in, and sit around.. who doesn't? hope everyone else is doing well.. "aisha yana" -jimmy

Things have changed for me again. Well it is now official. I am going to be broke for the rest of my life. I left work a half hour early today, so I could go get some brake pads installed on my car, and pay some bills.. I'm thinkin'.. $100 for the brake pads.. I can do that... Well.. NOPE!.. more than just the brake pads. about $930 worth. SO.. here's me.. back at square one. I am not going to pay $930 to fix that shit. I would rather put $930 down on a new car... So.. I'm in the car shopping market. Brand new.. fuck that used car shit.. In the mean time, I have to drive my brother's car (the one I drove in high school), which I don't trust to get me places at all. Would have been nice to still have that $745 I paid for the belts to get fixed... and the $300 for the Air Conditioning to get fixed... what a huge chunk of payments that could have been. *sighs* I can never catch a break... There goes my plans for... wait.. no... I am gonna get my own place, even if I am in debt. I can do it. There are things more important that getting DVDs and gadgets and trinkets... I have plenty already. I got so much shit.. and for some reason... I love living cheaply.. like generic foods.. coupons.. "buy 1 get 1 free - type things".. sounds amish, or ghetto, but I don't care.. I might as well take out some more loans too, for school... get more in debt.. there's no getting around it... I'm a BITCHER.. Bitching helps sometimes... As long as I have my Sidekick, Sirius Radio, and a car, I will be happy.. life offers more than those things... but I guess I'm not in a position for such things yet... Sorry If I Am A Bitch.. I'm me.. Jimmy

Yoda: "Failed to stop the Sith Lord, I have. Still much to learn, there is..." Qui-Gon (V.O.): "Patience. You will have time. I did not. When I became one with the Force I made a great discovery. With my training you will be able to merge with the Force at will. Your physical self will fade away, but you will still retain your consciousness. You will become more powerful than any Sith." Yoda: "Eternal consciousness." Qui-Gon (V.O.): "The ability to defy oblivion can be achieved, but only for oneself. It was accomplished by a Shaman of the Whills. It is a state acquired through compassion, not greed." Yoda: "...to become one with the Force, and influence still have...A power greater than all, it is. Qui-Gon (V.O.): "You will learn to let go of everything. No attachment, no thought of self. No physical self." Yoda: "A great Jedi Master, you have become, Qui-Gon Jinn. Your apprentice I gratefully become." this is a cut scene from Revenge of the Sith. hopefully it will be back in the DVD version...

<font color="blue">For the past few days, i have been feeding the animals at my neighbors, because they have been gone during Memorial weekend.  They live on a farm, and I was told to only feed the dog, and cats, so thats what I have been doing.  I go over there today and I feed them and I am about to leave, and I hear a loud noise coming from the barn.  So I start walking towards the barn and 3 huge pigs come running out ... and I'm like "Oh SHIT!!"  So I spent about an hour and a half chasing pigs.  Let me tell you, pigs are non-negotiable.  They are slow runners, but it's hard getting them to walk through a regular size doorway.  They aren't used to running, so a few times they would lay down and try and catch their breath.. well I guess I did too.  friggen pigs.

I just got done mowing the lawn.  I'm beat.  What movie should I watch?...  I know!

Jimmy

what can I say. Things are changing again. Work is getting... Well on Friday I went in to find out that someone in our department got fired. My boss told me who it was, and it's the guy they just hired about a month and a half ago. He helped out on the dock, to lighten up the work-loads. So now, we're back to being under-staffed, because he is gone, and another lady in our department has been gone for months, fighting cancer. It would be nice to get Alex out of the offices and helping on the dock. He is back for the summer. Friday was a half-day of work, so that was nice. Friday night I went over to Mike's and hung out with him and his girlfriend. We went to the Mall of America and looked around. After that, we met up with Matt (a different Matt than I usually talk about) and he went out and we all just talked about things going on in our lives, and they had some pretty good advice for me and I had some pretty good advice for them. It almost feels like I am a changed person after hearing what they had to say.. (no I'm not gay). It's about other things, irrelevant to write about in here. I guess some things can change for the good, for me at least, which is very rare. Saturday, I went to the Mall of America, again with Rick. I bought the Making of Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith, book. Did you know that if you don't use evasive action while you walk through the mall, people will walk right into you, and it's totally your fault. All in all, that mall is great for "people watching". And do I ever love Caribou Coffee? Heck yes I do. Watched the Harry Potter: And the Goblet of Fire trailer in the Apple store.. looks great! We saw Mindy and her mom shopping there. We hung out at Rick's after that, Mindy and Jill came over. Jill said, "Daddy, I'm freezing! Will you show me how to build a campfire?" and I said "ooh Campfire?" (with a japanese accent). So I built a campfire, with the help of some lighter fluid. We heard raccoons fighting in the trees also and I knocked over some flowers. Just great. I am just lazing around today. I get to see Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith again tonight! I can hardly wait. this will be my 4th time. It surely doesn't get old. In fact, in my opinion, it is the best of all six. It all ties in so perfectly, and it's just a beautifully made film. The people who hate the dialogue, oh well. You can make your own series of films and let's see how they turn out. I get tomorrow off, and I ain't doing shit. I am just going to sleep in, and relax, rarely do we get days off and I love sleeping in, so there. What should I do now?... I think I am going to put in Monty Python and the Holy Grail. Haven't watched that in a long-o-time. Hope your weekend is going well. later. Jimmy

well.. another day I am working right now, freakin' bored. It's noon and I haven't stopped to take a break yet today. I am just waiting for the help to get back from lunch, so I can get some. I'm starving.. *blah*.. I am done working at Roseville, thank god. Last friday I was on my way to work and my car just stopped working, while i was going 70MPH. So i had to get it towed and fixed. $745 later, I had my car back. So I am piss broke too. I am going to be looking for a second job, I wonder why I am even considering that.. I need money, but 8 hours of work is enough for me. in the past when I have wanted a second job, I never got around to applying. well, not much more to report.. but 36 hours, until Star Wars. Yippie hooray. hope everyone is having a great week. give me a call.. Jimmy

is this on? I haven't been online in a lonnng time.. well not long enough to do this. So here goes. Work- I wanna retire. But I suppose I am a little too young to consider that, so I will have to deal. I have been working at the Roseville location for the last 2 days, helping to get every last pallet out of there. It seems like it will never end. I think there is a light at the end of the tunnel though. It's kinda nice working at my own pace though, I don't have to stop everything to help a truck driver every two minutes, so I can actually finish my work. My bosses tell me I am doing "phenomenal" work. So we will see if the paychecks go up. That would be nice. Aveda offers reimbursment for schooling that applies to something work related there. So I am looking into taking advantage of that. My brother came home last weekend. He *sighs* ... he is so self-conscious. Everything is about him. I don't want to go into anything, but it just gets old. I got a Sirius Satellite Radio. It's nice to listen to commercial-free music whenever I go somewhere. I hear different songs, and not the same ones over, and over again. It's nice. I suggest getting one. A little more than a week until Star Wars III. Can't wait. I just want to see it without anything else being ruined, I want to enjoy it. I know I will, but even so. Wow! I have 4 new pillows now! and they are cold! heck yes they are! The Chronicles of Narnia looks like its going to be good. I should go read Goblet of Fire, or go watch Phantom Menace... either would be fun. This weekend is going to be busy.. matt and I are gonna do somethin, and I have a wedding to go to on Saturday. so good times all around. hope everyone is doing fine, and having a pleasant week ^^ -jimmy

well.. Monday is over. I have been really freakin' busy lately. Work has been extremely busy. I drove up to Moorhead, MN last Friday to visit my brother and bring some things home for him, since he is graduating. It's about 4 hours away, and 250 miles. I simply cannot wait... well I can,.. but.. you know... Sweet it's raining out right now.. another thing to keep this room cold.. I love cold pillows and sheets.. they are the absolute best. Next sunday I have to go back up to Moorhead for graduation.. *sigh* 2 weekends in a row.. but i wanna be there for by bro, ya know?... I hope everyone is having a great week! If you ever think about getting a Best Buy card. don't. they will mail your information to everyone. I got a bill today, for $130. I have never used the card, and I just got it about a month ago. The bill was very vague, didn't say who was billing me. It didn't have why I owed that. So I called the 1-800 number on the bill. Some lady picks up. just asks for my name, no account info and such. I asked her why they are billing me for the $130. She told me it was an annual fee for the Best Buy card. what?!? Best Buy doesn't have an annual fee for their card. She asks if I am able to make a payment over the phone or mail in?.. I ask her "can't I just go into any Best Buy and make a payment?.. Isn't there a customer service for doing that in every Best Buy?".. she said "No you have to do it by phone, internet, or mail in" ok with this information I told her, ok "I'm not paying this because A. I have never used the card, B. I have not even had the card for 1 month, C. There are no annual fees for having a Best Buy Card, and D. Any Best Buy will let you make a payment at the store."...... so she says "I will transfer you to customer care so you can cancel this account, please hold".... 30 seconds go by, I hear the recorded operator "If you would like to make a call..blah, blah, blah".. she hung up on me.. ok now I was more pissed, so I called back. I got the same lady. Now I'm thinking of Punch Drunk Love, if anyone can see the analogy to that. I tell her to cancel my card. She transfers me again... she tries 3 times, and says "Oh that department must be closed right now, I can put in a request to cancel your account, and reverse this bill since you haven't used the card." HMMM... most bill companies don't give up that easy, they make your ass pay it. I say "ok whatever" and hang up. I call the Best Buy number on the back of my card and the guy tells me "there is no annual fee" isn't this kind of thing considered illegal?.. i feel don't sorry for the idiots who have paid this "fake fee". I'm calling again tomorrow, to make sure whatever that shit is, got reversed, and that they know, I'm not paying for it. that's just my rant of the day. sorry if anyone read this.. have a good night/week Nooch Jimmy
